In article <931114.41340.TED89@delphi.com>,
Ted Kaliszewski  <TED89@delphi.com> wrote:
>Just how secure is the RSA system? I know all about the factoring problem
>so that is not what I have in mind. What about an internal threat? If you
>have any comment on the subject, please speak up. Thank you, Ted89.

No algoritm is secure against a "black bag" attack: someone bribing someone
to give them the key, someone threatening someone to give them the key,
someone sneaking in and stealing a key that was written down, etc.  This
is not cryptography.

Bruce
